title: Fixed the first bug encountered in the wild.
message:
Fixed the first bug encountered in the wild. 
If a cell was empty  (never been assigned before) it would not be returned in the cell feed, so the update method would do nothing. Had to add the return-empty parameter. Then realized that I was parsing the current value from Value instead of inputValue. The former is null, the latter is the empty string, and also makes more sense I think.

title: No behavioral changes, but I have the schemas set up for SQL database tables for…
message: No behavioral changes, but I have the schemas set up for SQL database tables for categories, months and expenses. All of these things will be saved to make an app that doesn't need to query all this stuff from the spreadsheet immediately every time it starts up, and that will allow expenses to be added while out crappy network connections are down.

title: This is the first version of Megabudget that does something useful. It:
message:
This is the first version of Megabudget that does something useful. It:
- populates the categories & months
- populates the total of the latest month
- you can select a category
- you can add an expense to that category

It has several notable problems
- no idea how it works when disconnected from the internet
- it is very slow, esp. at the beginning where it does multiple pulls from the spreadsheet
- you can't select a month

Additionally it would be really nice to 
- organize the categories by freq of use
- allow for offline expenses
